OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FSir Keir Starmer has vowed to listen
OL,8,Fto voters but refused to shift "left
OL,9,For right" despite pressure to change
OL,10,Fcourse and backbench calls for a new
OL,11,Fleader following Labour's electoral
OL,12,Fmauling.
OL,14,FThe Prime Minister said responding to
OL,15,F"tough" results, which saw Labour lose
OL,16,Fhundreds of councillors in England and
OL,17,Fsuffer humiliation in Wales, would
OL,18,Fmean "being assertive in our values"
OL,19,Fand "unifying rather than dividing".
OL,26,@pD@`OUqD@IO]wD@AOUwD@GO]zD@FOUzD@dO]{D@
OL,26,AEOU{D@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FThe ruling party haemorrhaged support
OL,8,Fin former strongholds while Reform UK
OL,9,Fmade stunning gains and Plaid Cymru
OL,10,Fbecame the largest party in a Senedd
OL,11,Felection that left outgoing First
OL,12,FMinister Eluned Morgan without a seat.
OL,14,FThe results have reignited rumblings
OL,15,Fof a leadership contest, with some
OL,16,Fbackbench MPs openly calling on Sir
OL,17,FKeir to set out a timetable for his
OL,18,Fdeparture and others urging an
OL,19,Fimmediate change in direction.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FBut in a defiant op-ed for the
OL,8,FGuardian, the Prime Minister wrote:
OL,9,F"While we must respond to the message
OL,10,Fthat voters have sent us, that doesn't
OL,11,Fmean tacking right or left.
OL,13,F"It means bringing together a broad
OL,14,Fpolitical movement, being assertive
OL,15,Fabout our values, bold in our vision
OL,16,Fand addressing people's demands.
OL,18,F"Unifying rather than dividing. That
OL,19,Fis the right approach for our party
OL,20,Fand, more importantly, it is the right
OL,21,Fapproach for our country."
OL,26,@qD@AOUuD@AOUzD@AOU}D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FHe said concerns expressed among
OL,8,Fdifferent communities have "more in
OL,9,Fcommon than some would like to admit,"
OL,10,Fwith the cost of living uniting voters
OL,11,Facross the board.
OL,13,F"Our job is to convince them that we
OL,14,Fhave progressive answers to the
OL,15,Fproblems and challenges that they
OL,16,Fface," Sir Keir said.
OL,26,@pD@\OUqD@fO]uD@AOUxD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FLabour also suffered from voters
OL,8,Fswitching to the Green Party as Zack
OL,9,FPolanski said the era of two-party
OL,10,Fpolitics "is not just dying, it is
OL,11,Fdead and it is buried".
OL,13,FFormer Cabinet minister Louise Haigh
OL,14,Ftold ITV Calendar: "I think what is
OL,15,Fabundantly clear is that unless the
OL,16,FGovernment delivers significant and
OL,17,Furgent change, then the Prime Minister
OL,18,Fcannot lead us into another election."
OL,26,@rD@JOUsD@VO]vD@TOUzD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FRichard Burgon, leader of the
OL,8,FSocialist Campaign Group of left-wing
OL,9,FLabour MPs, demanded Sir Keir set out
OL,10,Fa timetable for his departure.
OL,12,F"It is clear that Keir has fought his
OL,13,Flast election as Labour leader and,
OL,14,Fdeep down, he will know it," he said.
OL,16,FMr Burgon warned against a "stitch up"
OL,17,Fof the type that prevented Andy
OL,18,FBurnham from standing in the Gorton
OL,19,Fand Denton by-election.
OL,26,@tD@AOUvD@\O]xD@\OUxD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
