CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FThe Greater Manchester mayor is widely
OL,8,Fviewed as a potential challenger to
OL,9,FSir Keir if he can find a way to win a
OL,10,Fby-election to return to Westminster.
OL,12,FAndrea Egan, general secretary of the
OL,13,FUnison union, warned "Labour faces
OL,14,Fpolitical oblivion because it's simply
OL,15,Fnot delivering for the majority of
OL,16,Fpeople" and "there'll clearly be a
OL,17,Fchange of Labour leader sooner or
OL,18,Flater".
OL,26,@uD@VOUxD@GO]xD@MOUzD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FBut an apparently co-ordinated
OL,8,Fcampaign was mounted to shore up
OL,9,Fsupport for Sir Keir, with ministers
OL,10,Fand Labour grandees warning against
OL,11,Fthe disruption of a leadership contest.
OL,13,FTransport Secretary Heidi Alexander
OL,14,Fsaid the results were "brutal" but
OL,15,F"the last thing we need is to descend
OL,16,Finto a vanity leadership contest",
OL,17,Fwhile others warned against "navel-
OL,18,Fgazing" and "just blaming the boss".
OL,26,@vD@WOUvD@^O]wD@AOUxD@aO]yD@]OUzD@GO]zD@
OL,26,AMOUzD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778292207
OL,3,CStarmer refuses to shift 'left or
OL,4,Cright' amid pressure over electoral
OL,5,Cmauling
OL,7,FHealth Secretary Wes Streeting, who
OL,8,Fhas continued to attract speculation
OL,9,Fabout his ambitions despite publicly
OL,10,Fdenying plans for a leadership tilt,
OL,11,Fsaid the Prime Minister will "have my
OL,12,Fsupport" in setting out how the
OL,13,FGovernment will move forward on Monday.
OL,15,FBut facing questions from reporters on
OL,16,FFriday night as he attended the count
OL,17,Ffor Redbridge Council, where the party
OL,18,Fhopes to hold on to its majority, he
OL,19,Fdeclined to say whether he believed
OL,20,FSir Keir was the right person to lead
OL,21,FLabour into the next general election.
OL,26,@sD@^OUtD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
